relevant_findings.appearance: The patient appeared well but anxious.
relevant_findings.physical_exam: No rash, lymphadenopathy, or icterus was found. The lungs, heart, and abdomen were normal. No hepatosplenomegaly, flank mass, or costovertebral-angle tenderness detected. Pelvic examination revealed no abnormalities; no blood was seen at the urethral meatus. The arms and legs were unremarkable.
relevant_findings.urine_analysis: The urine was red and cloudy, positive (+++) for bile and albumin, and positive (++) for ketones. The sediment contained 5 to 10 white cells, innumerable red cells, and moderate numbers of bacteria per high-power field. The hematocrit was 39.3 percent. The white-cell count was 9400 per cubic millimeter.
